tree binary

                    Vulture
                   /      \
                  /        \
                 /          \
                /            \
            monkey            lion
            /    \            /   \
           /      \          /     \
        grass    fruit    zebra   giraffe


tree structure analsis

        Root: Vulture
        
        Left Subtree (rooted at monkey):
            - Left child: grass
            - Right child: fruit
            
        Right Subtree (rooted at lion):
            - Left child: zebra
            - Right child: giraffe
            
        Leaf Nodes: grass, fruit, zebra, giraffe


A) IN-ORDER TRAVERSAL
Rule: Left → Root → Right

Algorithm for In-order Traversal:

Algorithm: InOrderTraversal(node)
Input: Root node of tree (or subtree)

Step 1: If the node is NULL, return
Step 2: Recursively traverse the LEFT subtree (InOrderTraversal(node.Left))
Step 3: VISIT the current node (process node data)
Step 4: Recursively traverse the RIGHT subtree (InOrderTraversal(node.Right))
Step 5: End

Step-by-Step In-order Traversal:

Step 1: Start at root (Vulture) → go left to monkey
Step 2: At monkey → go left to grass
Step 3: At grass → left is NULL, so VISIT grass
        ✓ VISITED: grass
        
Step 4: Back to monkey → VISIT monkey (after left subtree done)
        ✓ VISITED: grass, monkey
        
Step 5: At monkey → go right to fruit
Step 6: At fruit → left is NULL, so VISIT fruit
        ✓ VISITED: grass, monkey, fruit
        
Step 7: Back to monkey → left and right done, back to root (Vulture)
Step 8: At Vulture → left subtree done, so VISIT Vulture
        ✓ VISITED: grass, monkey, fruit, Vulture
        
Step 9: At Vulture → go right to lion
Step 10: At lion → go left to zebra
Step 11: At zebra → left is NULL, so VISIT zebra
        ✓ VISITED: grass, monkey, fruit, Vulture, zebra
        
Step 12: Back to lion → VISIT lion (after left subtree done)
        ✓ VISITED: grass, monkey, fruit, Vulture, zebra, lion
        
Step 13: At lion → go right to giraffe
Step 14: At giraffe → left is NULL, so VISIT giraffe
        ✓ VISITED: grass, monkey, fruit, Vulture, zebra, lion, giraffe


In-order Traversal Result:
grass → monkey → fruit → Vulture → zebra → lion → giraffe

In-order Traversal Path Diagram:

                    Vulture (4)
                   /      \
                  /        \
                 /          \
                /            \
            monkey (2)        lion (6)
            /    \            /   \
           /      \          /     \
     grass (1)  fruit (3) zebra (5) giraffe (7)
     
Numbers in parentheses show visit order



B) PRE-ORDER TRAVERSAL
Rule: Root → Left → Right

Algorithm for Pre-order Traversal:

Algorithm: PreOrderTraversal(node)
Input: Root node of tree (or subtree)

Step 1: If the node is NULL, return
Step 2: VISIT the current node (process node data)
Step 3: Recursively traverse the LEFT subtree (PreOrderTraversal(node.Left))
Step 4: Recursively traverse the RIGHT subtree (PreOrderTraversal(node.Right))
Step 5: End


Step-by-Step Pre-order Traversal:

Step 1: Start at root (Vulture) → VISIT Vulture
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture
        
Step 2: Go left to monkey → VISIT monkey
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture, monkey
        
Step 3: Go left to grass → VISIT grass
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture, monkey, grass
        
Step 4: Back to monkey → go right to fruit → VISIT fruit
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture, monkey, grass, fruit
        
Step 5: Back to monkey → left and right done, back to Vulture
Step 6: At Vulture → go right to lion → VISIT lion
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture, monkey, grass, fruit, lion
        
Step 7: Go left to zebra → VISIT zebra
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture, monkey, grass, fruit, lion, zebra
        
Step 8: Back to lion → go right to giraffe → VISIT giraffe
        ✓ VISITED: Vulture, monkey, grass, fruit, lion, zebra, giraffe


Pre-order Traversal Result:
Vulture → monkey → grass → fruit → lion → zebra → giraffe

